{
  "texts": [
    "Speech-language pathology (SLP) is a dynamic healthcare discipline focused on the assessment, diagnosis, treatment, and prevention of communication and swallowing disorders.",
    "Speech-language pathologists (SLPs) serve people across the lifespan and practice in settings ranging from schools and hospitals to private and university clinics and research institutions.",
    "Their responsibilities span clinical care, education, advocacy, and leadership within and beyond the discipline.",
    "In recent years, artificial intelligence (AI) has emerged as a transformative force across many domains of healthcare.",
    "AI has brought to life ideas once found in the domains of science fiction (For examples of AI in daily living from science fiction literature, see Chiang, 2019)."
  ]
}